
[1]stablestand

   STABLESTAND, n. [stable and stand.] In law, when man is found at his
   standing in the forest with a cross bow bent, ready to shoot at a deer,
   or with a long bow; or standing close by a tree with grayhounds in a
   leash ready to slip. This is one of the four presumptions that a man
   intends stealing the kings deer.
